# System grid

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Overview
The System Grid is a simplified systems mapping tool used to visualize and analyze complex systems by breaking them down into key components.

## Purpose
The System Grid is used in R&D to gain a comprehensive understanding of a system, identify patterns and gaps, and spot potential leverage points for interventions.

## How it works
The tool uses a tabular format with columns representing stakeholders and rows representing issues or variables. Cells are filled with relevant information or insights, facilitating analysis and communication of systemic insights.

## Requirements
Facilitation and systems thinking skills, knowledge of the problem space and relevant stakeholders, diverse perspectives from system actors, rigorous desk research and field research, and collaborative analysis and synthesis.

## Reflections
Strive for comprehensiveness but prioritize critical stakeholders and issues. Iterate between mapping and research to refine the grid. Use the grid as an evolving knowledge management tool, not just a one-time exercise.

## Related methods (if any)

## Examples
The System Grid has been used in R&D to map complex systems such as nutrition and healthcare.
